# Trivy CVE allowlist — list specific CVE IDs to suppress, with a comment
# documenting why. Keep this list short and review on every dependency bump.
#
# Format: one CVE per line, optional `# <reason>` trailing comment.
#
# Examples:
#   CVE-2024-12345  # accepted — only exploitable via local file write, container is read-only root FS
#   CVE-2024-67890  # patched in upstream PR #123, awaiting downstream release
